		{
			description: [
				"You know the &aSheep&r well as the main source of &9wool&r. And they're certainly not bad choices; with the right genetics, sheep will out-produce any other woolen animals. The wooliest sheep can produce up to &64&r wool at a time!"
				""
				"If you decide to stick with the trusty sheep as your wool source, keep the following in mind:"
				""
				"- Some sheep are \"hair sheep.\" These will produce no wool, but can be harvested for &9leather&r."
				"- Some sheep are shedders, and will naturally drop &9wool&r without intervention."
				"- You can &9milk&r sheep after they have given birth."
				"- Sheep will give birth to &61-3&r lambs at a time."
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "alexsmobs:tab_icon"
				tag: {
					DisplayEntityType: "minecraft:sheep"
				}
			}
			id: "7A87C22347CB375D"
			optional: true
			tasks: [{
				id: "1B1099B3442D045A"
				title: "Sheep"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -8.0d
			y: -13.0d
		}
		{
			description: [
				"The &aLlama&r is a perfectly respectable source of &9wool&r. But only the fluffy ones can be sheared for &61&r wool; the rest are leather sources. "
				""
				"Here's what else you need to know:"
				""
				"- &aLlamas&r will give birth to &61&r baby at a time."
				"- Colder biomes will generally have fluffier &aLlamas&r."
				"- Make sure to tame the Wandering Trader's &aLlamas&r if you want to keep them."
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "alexsmobs:tab_icon"
